articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A protester with a Palestinian flag self-immolated on Friday outside the Israeli consulate in Atlanta, authorities said.
articles.title: Protester self-immolates outside Israeli consulate in Atlanta

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Panama published a ruling finding Canadian miner First Quantum's (FM.TO) contract for an open-pit copper mine in the Central American country unconstitutional in the official gazette on Saturday.
articles.title: Panama publishes ruling finding First Quantum contract unconstitutional

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Nicaraguan police late on Friday charged the owner of the local Miss Universe franchise with conspiracy, money laundering and spreading fake news, just weeks after the Central American nation's first victory in the pageant.
articles.title: Nicaragua's Miss Universe franchise owner accused of conspiracy

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The health of Pope Francis, who is suffering from a lung inflammation, is improving but he will read his Sunday message indoors from his residence to be on the safe side, the Vatican said on Saturday.
articles.title: Pope's condition improving but will stay indoors to be on safe side, Vatican says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Two Iranian Revolutionary Guards members who served as military advisers in Syria have been killed in an Israeli attack, Iranian state media reported on Saturday, in the first reported Iranian casualties during the ongoing war in Gaza.
articles.title: Iran says two revolutionary guards killed in Israeli attack in Syria

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's surge in respiratory illness is caused by known pathogens and there is no sign of new infectious diseases, a health official said on Saturday as the country faces its first full winter since lifting strict COVID-19 restrictions.
articles.title: China's respiratory illness rise due to known pathogens, official says

articles.author: Suhaib Salem, Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Renewed fighting in Gaza stretched into a second day on Saturday after talks to extend a week-old truce with Hamas collapsed and mediators said Israeli bombardments were complicating attempts to again pause hostilities.
articles.title: Renewed Gaza fighting stretches into second day after Israel-Hamas truce collapses

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Donald Trump does not have immunity from criminal charges for actions he took as president, a U.S. judge ruled on Friday, rejecting his bid to toss out the case brought by Special Counsel Jack Smith accusing him of unlawfully trying to overturn his 2020 election loss.
articles.title: Judge rejects Trump immunity claim in federal 2020 election case

articles.author: Max Hunder
articles.description: Ukraine's security service said on Saturday it had prevented former president Petro Poroshenko from leaving the country on grounds that Russia planned to exploit a planned meeting with Hungary's prime minister to hurt Ukrainian interests.
articles.title: Ukraine's security service alleges Russian plot involving ex-president

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: An earthquake of magnitude 7.5 struck Mindanao, Philippines on Saturday, the European-Mediterranean Seismological Centre (EMSC) said.
articles.title: Magnitude 7.5 earthquake strikes Mindanao, Philippines
